<item>
            <title>[LU-13141] Include block allocator improvements to additional distributions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13141</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This adds the block allocator performance enhancement introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12103&quot; title=&quot;Improve block allocation for large partitions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12103&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12103&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to CentOS 7.7, RHEL 8.x, Ubuntu 5.0 and 5.4 mainline kernels.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8212;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Block allocator uses some heuristic while choosing a group to allocate new blocks. This works good in most cases, but take a time for large low-free-space partition. The algorithm should be adjusted for this special case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
